bie.net/images/electric.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   How to make Napalm.</span><hr size=1> Found this at another forum. A kids gaming forum of all places. <br><br>DO NOT TRY THIS. EVER.<br><br>Get a plastic bucket, and a lid from Home Depot, along with some professional duct tape.<br><br>Go to the Gas Station and fill up the bucket 3/4 way with a combination of gasoline and kerosene. Premium gas will make a stronger napalm, because of the higher octane.<br><br>Grab all of the styrofoam you can, cups, boxing material, foam peanuts, anything petroleum based. Dissolve as much as possible, into the gasoline, stirring it with a wood stick. It will take a good 10 minutes.<br><br>Now, cover up the container with the lid, and seal it air tight with the duct tape, wrapping around it. Store this container for 3 weeks.<br><br>DO NOT LET THIS STUFF ANYWHERE NEAR ANY HEAT, KEEP IN IN THE SHADE OR ON ICE.<br><br>After 3 weeks, you will need good professional thick rubber gloves, because this napalm is acid, and will burn your hands.<br><br>This stuff is also very thick and sticky.<br><br>Be careful when you light this stuff on fire, NOTHING WILL BE ABLE TO EXTINGUISH THE FLAMES. Not water, not baking soda, not foam or even a fire extinguisher. NOTHING.<br><br>It'll take severeal days to burn if you used alot, maybe an hour for one tablespoon.<br> <p><br><a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace"><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~nuclearspace/website/images/title/title_03.jpg"> </a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uarkuunaves.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ArkuunAves</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Tourist</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/16/02 8:47:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5